rom the goal of Buddhahood. Duckworth probes deeply into Mipam's writings on Buddha-nature to illuminate its central place in a dynamic Buddhist philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aBuddhahood. 0aMādhyamika (Buddhism). 0aRi̧n-ma-pa (Sect)xDoctrines. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Buddhism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Tibetan Buddhism. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / Tibetan.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147798440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477984423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477984/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles